{
  "texts": [
    "Advanced manufacturing techniques further enhance thermal stability.",
    "Multi-junction solar cells with multiple semiconductor layers achieve higher efficiencies and are less susceptible to thermal losses.",
    "Thin-film solar cells, inherently less thermally sensitive, are suitable for a wider range of operating conditions (Ilse et al., 2019; Santhakumari & Sagar, 2019).",
    "To gain a deeper understanding of the impact of thermal effects on solar cell performance, it is instructive to examine real-world case studies across different geographic regions and climatic conditions.",
    "In this section, we present case studies that highlight the diverse challenges and solutions associated with thermal effects on solar cells, drawing upon relevant studies and data."
  ]
}